{"article_id":"cUpHGnGOOewO5O3W","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Police in Charleston , S.C. , say","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"a man","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"they suspect","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"opened fire","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"and killed nine people during a Wednesday prayer meeting at one of the city 's oldest historically black churches","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"has been captured .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Police are calling the attack a hate crime ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"and they released stills from a security video","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"that authorities say","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"show 21-year-old Dylann Roof entering the Emanuel African Methodist Episcopal Church .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"Roof ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"police said ,","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"sat with the congregation for about an hour","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"before he opened fire at around 9 p.m . ET .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"He left the church in a black sedan ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"unleashing an overnight manhunt","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"that involved local and federal law enforcement .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Police apprehended the lone suspect during a traffic stop in Shelby , N.C. , an almost four-hour drive from Charleston .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"Roof waived extradition during a court appearance in Shelby","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"and will be headed back to South Carolina .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"Charleston Mayor Joseph Riley said","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"the arrest is a part of the healing process","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"that has just begun .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"`` In America we do n't let people like this get away with this dastardly deed , ''","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"Riley said .","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"In a statement from the White House , President Obama meditated on the history of the church ,","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"which he called","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"a `` sacred place in the history of Charleston and in the history of America . ''","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"the Emanuel AME is a church","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"that has seen tragedy in the past .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"It was burned to the ground","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"because its worshippers wanted to end slavery .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"It 's a place","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"where civil rights leaders spoke","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"and led marches in search for freedom .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Obama said","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"it 's a tragedy anytime Americans die in a situation like this ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"but it 's especially heartbreaking","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"when it happens `` at a place","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"where people are seeking peace . ''","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Obama quoted a eulogy","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"Martin Luther King Jr.","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"delivered at the funeral service for three of the four children","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"who were killed in the 1963 bombing of a Baptist church in Birmingham .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"In death ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"King said ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"those three little girls told America","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"``","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"that we must be concerned not merely about who murdered them ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"but about the system , the way of life , the philosophy","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"which produced the murderers . ''","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"At an earlier press conference , Charleston Police Chief Gregory Mullen said :","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"`` It is senseless ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"it is unfathomable ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"that in today 's society somebody would walk into a church , into a prayer meeting ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"and take lives . ''","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"State Sen. Clementa C. Pinckney ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"who was also the senior pastor at Emanuel AME Church ,","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"was one of the people","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"killed during the attack .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"The President Pro Tempore of South Carolina 's Senate , Hugh Leatherman , said","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"Pinckney was `` a strong advocate for his constituents , a great pastor and community leader ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"but most importantly , a cherished and loved husband , father and son . ''","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"He continued :","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"`` The victims were in a Bible study ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"learning the Word of God , in one of the most beloved institutions in our State","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"whose roots go back to the dark days of slavery .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"What happened last night is incomprehensible . ''","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"The Charleston County coroner identified the nine victims as Cynthia Hurd , 54 ; Daniel Simmons Sr. , 74 ; Rev . Clementa Pinckney , 41 ; Rev . Sharonda Coleman-Singleton , 45 ; Ethel Lance , 70 ; Tywanza Sanders , 26 ; Myra Thompson , 59 ; Susie Jackson , 87 ; and Depayne Middleton Doctor , 49 .","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"All the victims , but Simmons , died at the scene .","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"Simmons died in hospital .","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"In a short speech at the White House , President Obama said","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"that he was restrained by what he could say about the facts of case ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"but he was not constrained by emotion .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"Obama said","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"that it is tragic","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"anytime Americans die in a situation like this .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"But it is especially heartbreaking","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"when it happens `` at a place","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"where people are seeking peace . ''","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"He said","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"the Emanuel AME is a church","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"that has seen tragedy in the past .","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"It was burned to the ground","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"because its worshippers wanted to end slavery .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"It 's a place","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"where civil rights leaders spoke","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"and led marches in search for freedom .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"`` This is a sacred place in the history of Charleston and in the history of America , ''","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"Obama said .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"Today ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"marks another attempt against a black church in the United States .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"like this church , and others like it , have rebuilt in the past ,","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"Mother Emanuel `` will rise again , now . ''","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"During a news conference , Charleston Police Chief Gregory Mullen said","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"a civilian called police","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"to report suspicious activity .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"Police followed up on the tip","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"and quickly figured out that they were dealing with shooting suspect Dylann Roof ,","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"who was arrested without incident .","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"Mullen ,","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"who would not comment on whether Roof had any weapons on him ,","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"said","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"that Roof was cooperative .","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"Mullen said","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"that police had yet to determine a motive .","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"Attorney General Loretta Lynch called the shooting in Charleston a `` barbaric crime . ''","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"`` Acts like this one have no place in our country","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"and no place in a civilized society , ''","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"Lynch said","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"that federal authorities are working closely with local authorities","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"to try to apprehend the suspect .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"President Obama is expected to make a statement at 11:45 a.m . ET .","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"A search of public records finds","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"that Dylann Roof had two recent court cases against him","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"- one for trespassing , one for drug possession .","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"The city of Charleston said","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"police have named a suspect :","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"21-year-old Dylann Roof .","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"`` The vehicle","depth":14},{"id":124,"text":"he may be driving","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"is a black Hyundai with vehicle tag LGF330 .","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"Anyone with information about his location call 1-800-CALL-FBI , ''","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"the city said in a statement .","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"The Southern Poverty Law Center ,","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"which tracks extremist groups ,","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"tweeted a photograph of the suspect","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"sporting a jacket with what appears to be the flag for `` white-rule Rhodesia , now Zimbabwe . ''","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"Another patch on the jacket ,","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"the SPLC says ,","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"shows a South African apartheid era flag .","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"The President Pro Tempore of South Carolina Senate , Hugh Leatherman , said","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"Sen. Pinckney was a `` beloved '' public servant .","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"`` Senator Clementa C. Pinckney was a leader in the Senate of South Carolina , a strong advocate for his constituents , a great pastor and community leader , but most importantly , a cherished and loved husband , father and son , ''","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"Leatherman said in a statement .","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"`` The entire Senate of South Carolina extends our love and sympathy to Jennifer , Eliana , Malana , and to the rest of his family . ''","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"Update at 9:05 a.m . ET .","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"State Senator Among Those Killed :","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"State Sen. Clementa C. Pinckney ,","depth":15},{"id":143,"text":"who was also the senior pastor at Emanuel AME Church ,","depth":15},{"id":144,"text":"was one of the people","depth":15},{"id":145,"text":"killed during the attack ,","depth":15},{"id":146,"text":"according to multiple news outlets as well as the chairman of the South Carolina Democratic Party .","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"`` Pinckney , 41 , is married","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"and has two children .","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"He was a Democratic member of the S.C. Senate . ``","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"State Rep. Wendell Gilliard said","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"he visited with Pinckney 's wife and two daughters after the shooting .","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"He said","depth":16},{"id":153,"text":"she is 'surrounded by friends . ' `` Gilliard arrived at the scene Wednesday night ,","depth":16},{"id":154,"text":"hearing chatter","depth":16},{"id":155,"text":"that Pinckney was killed by the gunman .","depth":16},{"id":156,"text":"' I did not want that to be true ;","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"I prayed","depth":15},{"id":158,"text":"it was n't true . ' ''","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"`` The Justice Department 's Civil Rights Division , the FBI , and the U.S. Attorney 's Office for the District of South Carolina are opening a hate crime investigation into the shooting","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"that took place at Emanuel AME Church in Charleston , SC .","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"The investigation is parallel to and cooperative with the state 's investigation . ''","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"Update at 7:17 a.m . ET .","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"Suspect Sat With Congregation For An Hour :","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"During a press conference just minutes ago , Charleston Police Chief Gregory Mullen said","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"the suspect sat with the congregation in prayer for about an hour","depth":14},{"id":166,"text":"before opening fire .","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"The suspect ultimately killed 9 people","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"- six females and three males .","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"Three others survived .","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"Mullen said","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"that law enforcement from all along the East Coast are helping in the investigation","depth":14},{"id":172,"text":"and the FBI and the ATF have come in from D.C .","depth":14},{"id":173,"text":"`` This tragedy","depth":16},{"id":174,"text":"that we 're addressing right now","depth":16},{"id":175,"text":"is indescribable , ''","depth":15},{"id":176,"text":"Mullen said .","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"`` No one in this community will ever forget this night ...","depth":14},{"id":178,"text":"and","depth":17},{"id":179,"text":"because of the pain and the hurt","depth":18},{"id":180,"text":"this individual has caused this community ...","depth":18},{"id":181,"text":"the law enforcement officials","depth":18},{"id":182,"text":"working on this","depth":18},{"id":183,"text":"are committed","depth":17},{"id":184,"text":"and we will catch this individual . ''","depth":15},{"id":185,"text":"Mullen called on anyone with information about the suspect to call 1-800-Call-FBI ,","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"but said","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"that they should not approach the suspect","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"because he is `` very dangerous . ''","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"Charleston Mayor Joseph Riley Jr. said","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"that last night that he and the police chief `` hugged as many '' of the victims ' families","depth":14},{"id":191,"text":"as they could .","depth":14},{"id":192,"text":"He said","depth":13},{"id":193,"text":"they saw weeping mothers , fathers , grandmothers and grandfathers .","depth":13},{"id":194,"text":"Riley said","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"this attack has ripped a part of the community 's fabric forever .","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"`` But we will work to heal them ,","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"to love them","depth":15},{"id":198,"text":"and support them in that church","depth":16},{"id":199,"text":"as long as we live , ''","depth":16},{"id":200,"text":"Riley said .","depth":13},{"id":201,"text":"According to The Post and Courier of Charleston ,","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"a gunman entered the church on Wednesday evening ,","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"as members of the church gathered for a prayer meeting .","depth":13},{"id":204,"text":"`` A female survivor told family members","depth":14},{"id":205,"text":"that the gunman initially sat down in the church for a bit","depth":15},{"id":206,"text":"before standing up","depth":16},{"id":207,"text":"and opening fire ,","depth":16},{"id":208,"text":"according to Dot Scott , president of the Charleston NAACP .","depth":13},{"id":209,"text":"`` The gunman reportedly told the woman","depth":14},{"id":210,"text":"he was letting her live","depth":15},{"id":211,"text":"so she could tell everyone else what happened ,","depth":15},{"id":212,"text":"Scott said .","depth":13},{"id":213,"text":"'' The Emanuel AME Church website says","depth":3},{"id":214,"text":"that church is the oldest African Methodist Episcopal church in the South .","depth":3},{"id":215,"text":"`` Emanuel has one of the largest and oldest black congregations south of Baltimore , Maryland , ''","depth":3},{"id":216,"text":"the website says .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":433,"left":429,"right":432,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":429,"left":241,"right":428,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":236,"right":240,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":222,"right":235,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":0,"right":221,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":221,"left":220,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":220,"left":1,"right":219,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":219,"left":2,"right":218,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":218,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":235,"left":232,"right":234,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":225,"right":231,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":225,"left":6,"right":224,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":224,"left":7,"right":223,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":231,"left":228,"right":230,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":228,"left":227,"right":13,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":227,"left":226,"right":12,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":226,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":14,"right":229,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":17,"right":233,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":233,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":240,"left":238,"right":239,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":20,"right":237,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":237,"left":21,"right":22,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":23,"right":24,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"N